transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Thiagra. This is Olivia speaking.

Speaker 2: Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 1: This is Barbara Lucas.

Speaker 2: Hi, Barbara. How are you?

Speaker 1: I'm fine, but I'm irritated.

Speaker 2: Why?

Speaker 1: My husband or I did not ask for that medication that they're sending, and we want that canceled immediately.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I know it's not your fault, but they've done that before.

Speaker 2: Right. Okay.

Speaker 1: So, yeah, I can help with the prescription as long as he's there and just gives me permission real quick to talk to you about it.

Speaker 2: Barry's standing right here.

Speaker 1: Oh, great. Okay.

Speaker 2: Barry, come here a minute.

Speaker 1: He did not order that, nor did I, and they've done that before.

Speaker 2: I just want it plain, canceled, and not to be ordered again.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Would you like to talk to him? He's standing here.

Speaker 1: Legally, I have to, yes, if you want to discuss his prescription.

Speaker 2: Is that what you would like?

Speaker 1: Right here, yes.

Speaker 2: Tell him he did not order that shit.

Speaker 1: Yes, I did not order that.

Speaker 2: So, sir, I don't even know who you are, right?

Speaker 1: So let's start at step one together, and we can see what we can accomplish.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: What is your first name?

Speaker 2: I can't hear you.

Speaker 1: What is your first name?

Speaker 2: Barry.

Speaker 1: Okay, Barry.

Speaker 2: What is the phone number that's going to be associated with your prescription?

Speaker 1: It's 717-903-4200.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: There you are.

Speaker 2: And what's your date of birth, Barry?

Speaker 1: 3-1-50.

Speaker 2: Great.

Speaker 1: And you're located at 344 Dressler Ridge Road, Millerson, Pennsylvania?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, great.

Speaker 2: And you give me permission to talk to your wife about your prescription, is that right?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, great.

Speaker 1: Thanks.

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Hi.

Speaker 2: So, yeah, no, I do see his Cialis prescription.

Speaker 1: So, yeah, I mean, if y'all don't want the recent refill, you don't have to receive it.

Speaker 2: You can send it right back to us for a refund.

Speaker 1: You just have to write return to sender on the packet.

Speaker 2: No, I do not want my account charged.

Speaker 1: I'm going to call the credit card company and tell them.

Speaker 2: And if it's charged, there's going to be trouble because they won't stop doing this.

Speaker 1: We did not order it.

Speaker 2: We do not want it.

Speaker 1: Do not charge our credit card account.

Speaker 2: Okay, so this prescription was actually started back in August 2023.

Speaker 1: Yes, ma'am, I know it was, but I had called them and told them no more.

Speaker 2: And they keep sending it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And it was supposed to be, huh?

Speaker 1: I don't have any record of you calling or who you spoke with.

Speaker 2: Do you know when you called or who you spoke with?

Speaker 1: No, I do not.

Speaker 2: But I called all over a year ago.

Speaker 1: I just want it canceled.

Speaker 2: I don't see why that's such a big deal.

Speaker 1: Just cancel it.

Speaker 2: Tell them don't send it.

Speaker 1: Because I will dispute it.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: I let it go before, but this time I will not.

Speaker 2: What's that?

Speaker 1: Nope, I heard you.

Speaker 2: You already threatened to do that, yes.

Speaker 1: Yes, I will.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: If you need anything else, I guess you know where to find us.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Has it been taken off?

Speaker 1: So like I mentioned, if you don't want to receive it, you don't have to.

Speaker 2: You just have to return it.

Speaker 1: You just have to write return to sender on the package,

Speaker 2: and they'll bring it right back to us, and we can refund you.

Speaker 1: But, yeah, the script is canceled, yes.

Speaker 2: So you canceled their subscription.

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: Prescription, I should say.

Speaker 1: Right, which you guys signed up for

Speaker 2: and have been receiving for two, three years now.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but we kept – I kept calling them every time

Speaker 1: and telling them not to send it anymore.

Speaker 2: We're here Monday through Friday, 8 to 5 Pacific, even on some holidays.

Speaker 1: I just don't have any record of you speaking with anybody.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: But, yeah, your prescription is canceled,

Speaker 2: and if you all want to send it back, you can,

Speaker 1: and I've let you know how to do that, and great.

Speaker 2: So you mean there's still one coming?

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: Yeah, and you were already charged for it, yes.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: I'll just have to get ahold of the credit card company.

Speaker 1: That's all I know to do.

Speaker 2: Well, I've offered you the option to return it, which is our policy,

Speaker 1: and like any business, it's the best we can do.

Speaker 2: So, yeah, if you want a refund, you can just write,

Speaker 1: return to sender on the unopened package, leave it in your post box,

Speaker 2: your post box, bring it right back to us, and we'll refund you.

Speaker 1: Okay, I will do that.

Speaker 2: All right, thanks.

Speaker 1: I hope you have a great day.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
